From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kSTEP <kstep@fix>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2026 05:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: Fix select_idle_sibling kthread stacking vs
 DELAYED_DEQUEUE

The per-cpu kthread stacking optimization in select_idle_sibling() checks
this_rq()->nr_running <= 1 without subtracting delayed-dequeued tasks.
When a per-cpu kthread is the only truly running task but delayed tasks
inflate nr_running, the check fails and the wakee is not stacked on the
kthread's CPU, breaking IO completion cache affinity.

Use the same correction applied by commit aa3ee4f0b754 ("sched/fair:
Fixup wake_up_sync() vs DELAYED_DEQUEUE") for wake_affine_idle():
subtract cfs_h_nr_delayed() from nr_running before the comparison.

Fixes: 152e11f6df29 ("sched/fair: Implement delayed dequeue")
Signed-off-by: kSTEP <kstep@fix>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index b00f16700f9c..a1b2c3d4e5f6 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -7822,7 +7822,8 @@ static int select_idle_sibling(struct task_struct *p, int prev, int target)
 	if (is_per_cpu_kthread(current) &&
 	    in_task() &&
 	    prev == smp_processor_id() &&
-	    this_rq()->nr_running <= 1 &&
+	    (this_rq()->nr_running -
+	     cfs_h_nr_delayed(this_rq())) <= 1 &&
 	    asym_fits_cpu(task_util, util_min, util_max, prev)) {
 		return prev;
 	}
